title: Facebook Tests Instagram Reels Integration In India
text: As part of a new test, Instagram will now give creators in India the chance to share short videos on Facebook. According to Bloomberg, this trial will allow a small number of users in India to share Instagram Reels — brief clips using augmented reality (AR) effects — on their Facebook newsfeeds.

title: Instagram Testing Reels Integration On Facebook Indian Accounts: Reuters
text: Facebook Inc (NASDAQ: FB) is reportedly testing a feature on Instagram enabling some Indian content creators to share short video clips, known as reels, on their Facebook accounts, Reuters reports. It will enable some Indian users to get their 30-second-long reels on Instagram recommended on Facebook.

title: Instagram's TikTok Clone ‘Reels' Is Coming To Facebook With Trial Starting In India
text: Reels was launched on Facebook-owned Instagram in August last year, but the short video service wasn't made available on Facebook's main platform at the time.
